            <!--
            TODO: Status view - shows live registration state across all sources.

            Primary table columns:
              hostname | IP | record type (A/AAAA) | PTR registered | source | in Unbound | status

            PTR is shown as a column on the forward record row (paired),
            not as a separate row - PTRs are almost always coupled to their
            forward record. PTR column shows checkmark if the corresponding
            in-addr.arpa or ip6.arpa record is present in Unbound.

            Sources:
              - Kea static reservations (kea-ctrl-agent API)
              - Kea active leases (kea-ctrl-agent API)
              - Unbound host_entries.conf (OPNsense-managed, shown for
                context but marked "not managed by this plugin")

            Status flags:
              - OK: forward + PTR both present in Unbound
              - Missing PTR: forward present but PTR absent
              - Stale: in local_data but not in any Kea source or host_entries
              - Static: in host_entries.conf, not managed by this plugin

            Secondary table: "Orphaned PTR records" - PTRs in local_data
            with no corresponding forward record. Rare but possible if daemon
            crashed between adding the forward record and the PTR, or if
            something else injected PTRs directly. Flagged for review.

            Optional action: remove stale/orphaned records after confirmation.
            Backed by audit mode of kea-unbound-sync.py (not yet implemented).

            <Status order="50" VisibleName="Status" url="/ui/keaunbound/status"/>
            -->
